ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: This child finds it hard to make friends  OR  For this child it's pretty easy
Notes: 1 = Really True for me (left); 2 = Sort of True for me (left); 3 = Sort of True for me (right); 4 = Really True for me (right); -99= Missing Value

ElementDescription: This child is usually well-behaved OR This child is often not well-behaved
Notes: 1=Really True (Left); 2=Sort of True (Left); 3=Really True (Right); 4=Sort of True (Right)

ElementDescription: This child has social skills to make friends  OR  This child doesn't have social skills to make friends
Notes: 4 = Really True for me (left); 3 = Sort of True for me (left); 2 = Sort of True for me (right); 1 = Really True for me (right); -99= Missing Value

ElementDescription: This child usually acts appropriately OR This child usually does not act appropriately.
Notes: 1=Really True (Left); 2=Sort of True (Left); 3=Really True (Right); 4=Sort of True (Right)

ElementDescription: This child knows how to become popular  OR  This child does not know how to become popular
Notes: 4 = Really True for me (left); 3 = Sort of True for me (left); 2 = Sort of True for me (right); 1 = Really True for me (right); -99= Missing Value

ElementDescription: This child often gets in trouble because of the things he/ she does OR This child usually doesn't do things that get him/ her in trouble.
Notes: 1=Really True (Left); 2=Sort of True (Left); 3=Really True (Right); 4=Sort of True (Right)

ElementDescription: Compared to other children This child's age, This child has very good social skills OR Compared to other children This child's age, This child does not have very good social skills.
Notes: 1=Really True (Left); 2=Sort of True (Left); 3=Really True (Right); 4=Sort of True (Right)

ElementDescription: My child has a lot of friends.. OR My child doesn't have a lot of friends..
Notes: 4 = Really True for me (left); 3 = Sort of True for me (left); 2 = Sort of True for me (right); 1 = Really True for me (right)

ElementDescription: My child is popular with other kids their age OR My child is not popular with other kids their age
Notes: 4 = Really True for me (left); 3 = Sort of True for me (left); 2 = Sort of True for me (right); 1 = Really True for me (right)
